#dev #workflow

> Install, test, and watch commands for working on this project.

How to work on this project.

Install (dev mode):
  pip install -e ".[dev]"

Run tests:
  pytest                                                    # full suite
  pytest tests/test_parser.py::TestParseTags::test_single_tag  # single test

Run the watcher (keep DB live while editing notes):
  eshp watch

Query the memory graph:
  eshp scan <query>        broad discovery (FTS + tags + 1-hop expansion)
  eshp recall <slug>       focused context load (full note + N related)
  eshp show <slug>         single note with edges
  eshp tag <tagname>       notes by tag
  eshp rels                all relationship types with counts
  eshp edges [--rel REL]   all src --[rel]--> dst triples

Bootstrap skills for an AI agent:
  eshp init-skills .github/skills    # GitHub Copilot
  eshp init-skills .cursor/skills    # Cursor (or any agent path)

The DB (.eshp.db) lives inside the eshp/ directory.
It is gitignored — regenerated from .eshp files via `eshp watch` or sync().

Key test files:
  tests/test_parser.py  — parser + render tests
  tests/test_store.py   — store upsert/delete/query tests
  tests/test_cli.py     — CLI command tests (init-skills)

